<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1006">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1006">
Female. This species is easily distinguishable from all Echthronomas species in having a transversely wrinkled propodeum, black clypeus with two yellow lateral spots, black face and malar space (Fig. 3a), black fore coxae with red (yellowish) spots, black metasoma with red postpetiole apically and tergites 
<normalizedToken originalValue="II–IV">II-IV</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 3b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1006">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthronomas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthronomas tricincta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricincta">Echthronomas tricincta</taxonomicName>
(Gravenhorst, 1829) differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthronomas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthronomas quadrinotata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotata">Echthronomas quadrinotata</taxonomicName>
(Thomson, 1887) in having entirely yellow fore and mid coxae, clypeus, and malar space, partly yellow face, and a black metasoma with only red apically tergites 
<normalizedToken originalValue="II–IV">II-IV</normalizedToken>
. Another species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthronomas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthronomas ochrostoma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochrostoma">Echthronomas ochrostoma</taxonomicName>
(Holmgren, 1860), is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Echthronomas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Echthronomas quadrinotata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotata">Echthronomas quadrinotata</taxonomicName>
(Thomson, 1887), but differs in having a yellow malar space and clypeus (sometimes with a small black central spot) (
<bibRefCitation author="Horstmann, K." journalOrPublisher="Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="1006" pagination="57 - 67" title="Die europaeischen Arten der Gattung Echthronomas Foerster and Eriborus Foerster (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae)" volume="36" year="1987">Horstmann 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
